-- Portugal Signs Eight Mining Contracts Worth 3.8 Million Euros
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-12-07T10:42:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-07/portugal-signs-eight-mining-contracts-worth-3-8-million-euros.html
The  Portuguese government  signed
eight mining contracts worth 3.8 million euros with companies
interested in searching for gold, silver, wolfram and other
resources in the southern European country.  “This is a sector that is in clear expansion,” Economy
Minister Alvaro Santos Pereira told reporters today in Lisbon.  Portugal’s government has signed about 95 mining contracts
since it came into power last year, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
